R1  over the sum of the two
resistors R1 plus R2

106
00:06:24,793 --> 00:06:30,246
to which we add the component due to

107
00:06:30,246 --> 00:06:33,819
the supply at the excitation U0,

108
00:06:35,699 --> 00:06:41,153
and so we represent the circuit without
the supply i0.

109
00:06:43,601 --> 00:06:50,436
R1 is here with the voltage supply U0,

110
00:06:50,671 --> 00:06:52,642
the only one we consider in this
second exercise

111
00:06:52,642 --> 00:06:54,196
of this second part.

112
00:07:02,836 --> 00:07:08,624
And here, the part 0 which is from 
i0 to have a null current

113
00:07:09,395 --> 00:07:12,763
and so we have the second component i2b

114
00:07:12,763 --> 00:07:18,019
which is given by the supply U0.

115
00:07:23,055 --> 00:07:26,789
So this term i2b is simply

116
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:33,670
the ratio of U0 over the sum of
the resistors R1 plus R2.

117
00:07:37,417 --> 00:07:39,047
In this particular example,

118
00:07:39,467 --> 00:07:45,039
we see that the current i2a and the
current i2b are going in the same direction

119
00:07:45,039 --> 00:07:46,479
which is why we add them,

120
00:07:46,922 --> 00:07:48,515
but in another example

121
00:07:48,515 --> 00:07:54,416
one of the two currents might be in the opposite
direction to the current one has made default

122
00:07:54,416 --> 00:07:56,966
going towards the bottom in the
original drawings,

123
00:07:57,337 --> 00:07:59,265
in which case we would have to
subtract this current.

124
00:07:59,734 --> 00:08:01,299
In conclusion, we can say

125
00:08:01,299 --> 00:08:04,551
that from a relatively complex circuit

126
00:08:04,551 --> 00:08:08,562
composed of more than one excitation,
by applying the superposition principle

127
00:08:08,562 --> 00:08:11,340
we can get circuits,

128
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:15,594
a certain number of circuits,
that are easier to deal with

129
00:08:16,452 --> 00:08:22,155
and by adding the results we
get the global result.

130
00:08:22,423 --> 00:08:24,338
One must keep in mind

131
00:08:24,338 --> 00:08:27,157
that the elements must be linear
on one hand

132
00:08:27,157 --> 00:08:31,473
and on another hand pay attention
to the signs of the currents

133
00:08:31,473 --> 00:08:32,668
and voltages obtained.
